        "name": "Marten River Provincial Park",
        "stop": "Temagami",
        "category": "Nature",
        "desc": "Gateway to the Temagami wilderness and a living museum of Northern Ontario's logging heritage. A replica 19th-century logging camp sits among towering pines along the Transition Trail. Three sandy beaches on the Marten River are perfect for swimming. Horseshoes, beach volleyball, hiking, canoeing, and fishing. Every third weekend of July the park hosts Lumberjack Days - live music, logging contests, and traditional food. Less than one hour from North Bay and a natural stop between North Bay and Temagami along Highway 11.",
